      public SavingAccount​(int accountNumber, java.lang.String name, int cvv, java.lang.String expiryDate, java.lang.String type, java.lang.String password, double balance)
      The primary constructor for a savings account.
      Parameters:
      accountNumber - the account number associated with the account
      name - the username for the account
      cvv - the card verification value for the account
      expiryDate - the expiration date of the account
      type - the account type (chekcing or savings)
      password - the password for the account
      balance - the balance of the account

    • accountNumGenerator

      public int accountNumGenerator()
      The accountNumGenerator method is used to generate an account number upon creation of a new account. The account number formula is 800001+number of current savings accounts.
      Specified by:
      accountNumGenerator in interface Account
      Overrides:

      Returns:

    • withdraw

      public void withdraw​(double amount)
      The withdraw method is called to withdraw money from the account and charges a $5 transaction fee for withdrawal. This method also adds a withdrawal transaction to the transaction list.
      Specified by:
      withdraw in interface Account
      Overrides:
      withdraw in class CheckingAccount
      Parameters:

    • moneyTransfer

      public void moneyTransfer​(Account obj, int amount)
      The moneyTransfer method is called to transfer money from the account to another external account and charges a $2 transfer fee. This method also adds a money transfer transaction to the transaction list.
      Parameters:
      obj - the external account that money should be transferred to.
      amount - the amount of money that should be transferred.ey in dollars of type double.
